01/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- The government expects to open negotiations with the EU on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement by the end of the year, according to a government press release issued Sunday (30 September). 
Authorities say they have met all preliminary conditions for launching negotiations. 
In separate remarks on relations between Albania and the United States, Prime Minister Fatos Nano said his government is "committed to carrying out reforms in the public administration, and will continue to fight fiscal evasion, organised crime and illegal trafficking." (Albanian News, ATA - 30/09/02)
